  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Rate of appendix localization on ultrasound is not high. We suggest a way to improve it's
      localization by oral administration of iodinated contrast material.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The administration of oral iodinated contrast material might facilitate identification of the
      appendix and accurate diagnosis of appendicitis. When indicated will shorten time to CT
      examination.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
